{
  "stem": "8784.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "Evidently, Amon Goeth had his orders to liquidate and kill as many people as he can in order to close down that camp because the Russians were advancing rapidly at this time.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "In October of 1944 this was.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "Unbeknown to me, the 300 of us that were remnants in Oskar Schindler's factory, the 300 of those people, together with 400 others and the-- and the women, and the 300 women, were loaded into cattle cars for shipment someplace, to somewhere.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "The men, the 700 men, were loaded up in Krakow-Plaszow.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "And while we didn't know our destination at all, and we knew nothing about Oskar Schindler-- if there were some people in our group that knew about Oskar Schindler, there-- they knew it.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "I did not.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 62,
      "text": "So we were loaded up into cattle cars, and the women were shipped to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 63,
      "text": "The men were shipped to Gross-Rosen.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 64,
      "text": "In October of 1944, we arrived in Gross-Rosen.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 65,
      "text": "It was extremely cold already at that time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 66,
      "text": "When we arrived in Gross-Rosen, the-- we were greeted there by-- by brutal SS guards.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 67,
      "text": "Most of those SS guards in the Krakow-- in the Gross-Rosen camp were volunteers-- Lithuanians, Ukrainians, Poles, and extremely brutal people.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 68,
      "text": "When we arrived there, they quickly ordered us into formations.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 69,
      "text": "There were latrines there that we finally could relieve ourselves of because we were packed into the cattle cars for all this time.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 70,
      "text": "And we--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The trip took someplace-- 7, 10 days.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I really would have absolutely no 100% knowledge of what it was.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was many days, many shipments.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The rail-- the cattle cars were shifted from siding to siding because of the-- the trip could have been very short.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
